title: About Me:
text:
I am a second-year ScM student in cancer epidemiology at Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health under the mentorship of Dr. Avonne Connor.
I am also a contractor at the National Cancer Institute, Division of Cancer Epidemiology & Genetics under the mentorship of Dr. Nicolas Wentzensen and Dr. Megan Clarke.
I am passionate about prevention, early detection and survivorship of gynecologic and anogenital cancers and am currently applying for PhD programs!
Check out my research here!

title: Hi! I’m Camryn Cohen
text:
Welcome to My Website!


I’m a cancer epidemiologist in training, studying gynecologic and anogenital cancers!
I’m originally from Sarasota, FL but currently live in Baltimore, MD. I love powerlifting, pilates, spending time outdoors, watching reality TV and hanging out with my friends & family!
